prompt:
Create an educational medical cartoon panel in Dora the Explorer style.

Educational cartoon in Dora the Explorer style:
- Thick black outlines (3-4 pixels) around ALL elements
- Flat, vibrant colors with NO gradients or shading
- Simple, clean shapes
- Large expressive eyes (30% of face size)
- Cheerful, friendly character design
- Clear visual hierarchy
- Landscape orientation (1536×1024 pixels)

CHARACTERS: Dr. Young Erben, Surgical residents, Fellows
- Dr. Young Erben: Korean woman, petite build, 40s, wearing rectangular expressive black-framed glasses, black hair in neat ponytail, teal scrubs (#008B8B) or surgical greens (#2F4F4F) depending on scene, warm smile, professional demeanor

SCENE: Dr. Erben discussing case with team

KEY VISUAL ELEMENTS: Conference room, Before/after images, Teaching moment

DIALOGUE/TEXT: "Distal bypasses are challenging but save limbs. Each patient deserves this chance." (Distal bypasses are challenging but save limbs. Each patient deserves this chance.)

EDUCATIONAL FOCUS: Surgical education and mentorship

IMPORTANT SPECIFICATIONS:
- Thick black outlines (3-4px) on EVERYTHING
- Flat colors, NO gradients
- Large expressive cartoon eyes
- Clean, simple shapes
- Landscape format 1536×1024
- Medical accuracy in anatomical elements
- Warm, reassuring tone
- Spanish text with English subtitles where applicable
